		<td><b>Mario Bros - The Revenge (ROM-hack)</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Why aren't there any job-openings for NES ROM-hacking? I love this stuff, getting buried in 6502-code, trying to find out what's happening. <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /><br />I've lost count on how many hours I've spent on this one. There's lots and lots. I'm probably nuts. Or I am now anyway.<br /><br />I've alwayed loved the original &quot;Mario Bros&quot; for NES. I have very fond memories of long playsessions with my brother during christmas when we got it back in the 80's.<br />So, interested in the algorithms and technologies used in the game, I decided to create my own little hack.<br /><br />Anyway, if you like this game aswell, you might like this one<br />* Added a short intro cutscene (sort of <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" />)<br />* Game B is alot harder, for serious POWER-PLAYERS only. Two-player sessions would be totally insane. <img src="./images/smilies/icon_wink.gif" alt=";)" title="Wink" /><br />* Gathering coins is now a good idea, since collecting 25 of them gives you an extra life.<br />* Somewhat modified attackwaves.<br /><br />You can get it here:<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.romhacking.net/hacks/1778/">http://www.romhacking.net/hacks/1778/</a><!-- m -->

		

		</td>
	</tr>
