		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">oRBIT2002 wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Why aren't there any job-openings for NES ROM-hacking?</div><br />Because copyright owners tend to attack paid projects more than free ones. That said, <em>Donkey Kong</em> and <em>Mario Bros.</em> got official hacks in the past couple years, as did a few Virtual Console games that had used seizure-tastic backgrounds (e.g. <em>Zelda II: The Adventure of Link</em>) or product placement (e.g. the big <em>Tetris</em> ad that is <em>Zoda's Revenge: StarTropics II</em>).

		

